UID:quin-event-175068@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260302
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260401
SUMMARY:A Taste of Rome
LOCATION:Café Q
DESCRIPTION:Category: Food & Beverage\nPrice: Free / Included\nStatus: Avai
 lable\nTime: 5 PM – 9 PM\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/ev
 ents/175068\n\nLet your palate wander to the Eternal City with our A Taste
  of Rome dinner experience\, celebrating the soulful\, time-honored flavor
 s of Italy’s capital. Available exclusively during dinner service\, this
  limited-time offering honors Rome’s culinary tradition—where simplici
 ty and exceptional ingredients take center stage.\n\nBegin with Bruschetta
  alla Romana\, bright with cherry tomato\, caper\, garlic confit\, and bas
 il on toasted ciabatta. Savor golden Gnocchi alla Romana in pomodoro with 
 Parmigiano Reggiano\, and the beloved Spaghetti alla Carbonara\, where gua
 nciale\, pecorino romano\, and egg yolk come together in perfect harmony. 
 For the main course\, Saltimbocca with Vignarola pairs tender veal\, prosc
 iutto di San Daniele\, sage\, and a vibrant spring vegetable ragù.\n\nEac
 h dish reflects Rome’s effortless balance of rustic authenticity and qui
 et refinement.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175068
CATEGORIES:Food & Beverage
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-174457@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260304T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260304T100000
SUMMARY:Private Art Tour: "An Indigenous Present" 
LOCATION:ICA Boston
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free / Included\nStatus: unlimited\n
 Event URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/174457\n\nJoin us for a
  private tour of the exhibition: An Indigenous Present\, before the Instit
 ute of Contemporary Art Boston opens its doors to the public\, led by Cura
 torial Assistant Max Gruber. Co-organized by 'Quin Collection artist Jeffr
 ey Gibson and independent curator Jenelle Porter\, An Indigenous Present�
 �offers an expansive view of Indigenous art practices over the past 100 ye
 ars\, highlighting a continuum of elders and emerging makers\, as well as 
 premiering new\, site-specific works by fifteen artists\, including Raven 
 Chacon\, Caroline Monnet\, and Anna Tsouhlarakis. Together\, we'll explore
  these artists' diverse approaches to concept\, form\, and medium within t
 he larger context of Native North American artistic tradition.\n\n*This ev
 ent is complimentary and reserved for members only.The tour will run for a
 pproximately one hour\, followed by time for members to continue exploring
  the exhibition at their leisure. Food and beverage will not be offered du
 ring this tour. Please be aware that the ICA Boston does not have designat
 ed parking. There is a Public Parking Garage located at 100 Northern Aven
 ue\, with the entrance being on Harbor Shore Drive\, across the street fr
 om the museum.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/174457
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
