BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-170316@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260309T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260309T210000
SUMMARY:Author's Circle Book Club: "Gorgeous Excitement" with Cynthia Weine
 r 
LOCATION:The Muse
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 2 spots left\nSt
 atus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/170316
 \n\nBookmark the date for a compelling conversation exploring Gorgeous Exc
 itement\, the dazzling debut novel by Cynthia Weiner that captures the ele
 ctric allure\, and quiet disillusionment\, of coming of age in 1980s New Y
 ork City.\n\nSet against the backdrop of downtown Manhattan’s art scene\
 , the novel follows Nina Jacobs\, a young woman newly arrived in the city 
 and determined to remake herself amid a world of glamour\, excess\, and cr
 eative ambition. As Nina is drawn deeper into a seductive orbit of artists
 \, parties\, and possibility\, the excitement of reinvention gives way to 
 reckoning\, forcing her to confront the cost of desire\, identity\, and be
 longing.\n\nAt once vivid and introspective\, Gorgeous Excitement explores
  the tension between aspiration and authenticity\, the intoxicating pull o
 f youth\, and the moment when fantasy collides with reality. Join us for a
  thoughtful discussion of Weiner’s evocative portrait of self-discovery\
 , ambition\, and the price of wanting more.\n\n*This event is complimentar
 y and reserved for members only. Complimentary light bites and beverages w
 ill be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/170316
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
