BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-174816@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260311T183000
SUMMARY:Author Talk: Eat\, Drink\, and Be Healthy
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: Health & Wellness\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 1 spot 
 left\nStatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/event
 s/174816\n\n5:00PM Reception\, 5:30PM Discussion \nJoin us for an evening
  of thoughtful inquiry with Dr. Walter Willett - physician\, epidemiologis
 t\, and Professor of Epidemiology and Nutrition at the Harvard T.H. Chan S
 chool of Public Health - whose scholarship has fundamentally shaped modern
  understanding of diet and disease.\n\nOver four decades\, and during his 
 25-year tenure as Chair of Harvard’s Department of Nutrition\, Dr. Wille
 tt has led landmark research examining how daily food choices influence th
 e development of heart disease\, cancer\, and other major illnesses. Drawi
 ng on data from vast\, long-running cohort studies encompassing nearly 300
 \,000 participants\, his work has elevated nutritional epidemiology from e
 merging discipline to cornerstone of preventive medicine.\n\nThe most cite
 d nutritional scientist in the world and a member of the National Academy 
 of Medicine\, Dr. Willett will reflect on the evolving science of nutritio
 n and consider how rigorous research can inform more discerning\, health-c
 onscious decisions in our daily lives.\n\n*This event is complimentary and
  reserved for members only. Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/174816
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
END:VEVENT
