BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175758@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T190000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: The Commonwealth at The Oscars
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist Only\nEve
 nt URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175758\n\n5:30PM Reception
 \, 6:00PM Discussion \nJust in time for the Academy Awards\, we invite yo
 u to an engaging reflection on Massachusetts-made films and the Commonweal
 th’s enduring connection to Hollywood’s biggest night. From Good Will 
 Hunting and The Departed to Best Picture winners like Spotlight and CODA\,
  Boston-born stories and talent have long shaped the Oscars stage.\n\nJoin
  Meg Montagnino-Jarrett\, Director of the Massachusetts Film Office\, in c
 onversation with Angela Peri\, Founder of Boston Casting\; acclaimed local
  actress Rena Maliszewski\, whose credits include Oscar-winning CODA and T
 he Holdovers\; and Locations Director Stephen Hartman. Together\, they wil
 l explore the scripts\, performances\, and behind-the-scenes craftsmanship
  that have positioned Boston as a powerful force in contemporary cinema.\n
 \nAn evening for film enthusiasts and cultural insiders alike\, this conve
 rsation offers a rare look at the creative ecosystem that continues to bri
 ng award-winning storytelling to life—right here in the Commonwealth.\n\
 n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members only. Light bites a
 nd refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175758
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
