BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175759@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260317T183000
SUMMARY:Author Talk: "The Encore" with Juliet Izon
LOCATION:Scotties
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 79 spots left\nS
 tatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/17575
 9\n\n5:00PM Reception\, 5:30PM Discussion\nAn unforgettable story of ambit
 ion\, music\, and second chances\, “The Encore” marks the striking deb
 ut of Juliet Izon.\n\nSpanning two decades - from the halls of Boston’s 
 elite Brookfield Conservatory to a rock tour bus careening cross-country -
  the novel traces a once-unbreakable bond between a gifted pianist and a r
 ising composer\, a single night that alters their futures\, and the teenag
 e piano virtuoso who ultimately forces them to confront the past. Sweeping
  and emotionally charged\, The Encore explores the cost of artistic devoti
 on\, the complexities of friendship\, and the enduring resonance of unfini
 shed melodies.\n\nA journalist whose work has appeared in The New York Tim
 es and The Wall Street Journal\, Izon brings a sharp insider’s perspecti
 ve and lyrical depth to this compelling story set against the intoxicating
  backdrop of the music industry.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reser
 ved for members only. Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175759
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-173832@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260317
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260321
SUMMARY:Explorateur: Wild Honey Inn 
LOCATION:Café Q
DESCRIPTION:Category: Food & Beverage\nPrice: Free / Included\nStatus: Avai
 lable\nTime: 5:30 PM – 10 PM\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.co
 m/events/173832\n\nExplorateur returns to The ‘Quin House in celebration
  of St. Patrick’s Day\, welcoming back acclaimed Chef Aidan McGrath of W
 ild Honey Inn\, Ireland’s first Michelin-starred pub and still the only 
 one to hold this distinction. \n\nFollowing an unforgettable debut reside
 ncy\, Chef Aidan makes his highly anticipated return for a four-day reside
 ncy in Café Q\, where he will present both a bespoke prix-fixe menu and a
 n à la carte dinner menu exclusively for ‘Quin members. His cooking rei
 magines the Irish dining pub experience\, elevating it with refined techni
 que while preserving the warmth and convivial spirit of a traditional coun
 try inn.\n\nMembers can look forward to Diver Scallops with pea velouté\;
  Wild Nova Scotia Halibut with tapenade velouté\; Spring Australian Lamb 
 with black olive jus\; and Wagyu Corned Beef with choux farci and mustard 
 butter sauce — refined interpretations of Irish tradition.\n\nIn additio
 n to the full dining experience in Café Q\, members may also enjoy a sele
 ction of Chef Aidan’s specials offered in the Pub throughout the residen
 cy. \n\nRooted in the Burren region of County Clare\, an area of striking
  natural beauty along Ireland’s rugged west coast\, Chef Aidan’s cuisi
 ne draws inspiration from the land\, sea\, and seasons. Throughout his res
 idency\, locally sourced ingredients are transformed with masterful creati
 vity and restraint. \n\nView the Menu.\n\nTo secure your reservation in e
 ither Café Q or The Pub\, please click here.\n\n*The prix-fixe dinner is
  priced at $85++ per person\, exclusive of beverages\, tax\, and applicabl
 e club fees. An à la carte menu will also be available\, with items price
 d individually. Reservations may be made through the Member Portal. Member
 s may invite up to three guests per seated member.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/173832
CATEGORIES:Food & Beverage
END:VEVENT
