DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T120000
SUMMARY:Hands on Impact: Greater Boston Food Bank 
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Impact Fund\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist On
 ly\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175767\n\nJoin The 
 ’Quin Impact Fund for a hands-on volunteer experience at the Greater Bos
 ton Food Bank\, where members can make a tangible difference in the fight 
 against hunger across our community. Participants will help sort\, package
 \, and organize food donations that support thousands of neighbors in need
  throughout Greater Boston.\n\nThe Greater Boston Food Bank (GBFB)\, New E
 ngland’s largest hunger-relief organization and a member of Feeding Amer
 ica\, distributed 107 million pounds of nutritious food last year alone. T
 hrough the dedication of its staff\, volunteers\, and partners\, GBFB work
 s to provide three meals a day to every person in need in Eastern Massachu
 setts\, supporting healthy lives and thriving communities.\n\n*This event 
 is complimentary and reserved for members only. Please wear comfortable cl
 othing suitable for service and close-toed shoes.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175767
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Impact Fund
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-167855@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T120000
SUMMARY:'Quin Impact Fund: Winter Walk
LOCATION:Meet in Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Impact Fund\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist On
 ly\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/167855\n\nThe ’Qu
 in Impact Fund invites members to take part in Winter Walk\, a powerful ca
 ll to action to help end homelessness in our city. This annual two-mile wa
 lk offers an opportunity to gather in solidarity and experience\, if only 
 briefly\, the winter conditions faced by Boston’s unhoused neighbors.\n\
 nMembers are encouraged to meet at The ’Quin for complimentary hot bever
 ages and coordinated ’Quin Impact Fund hats before walking together to B
 oston Common for the official program. The morning will include remarks an
 d storytelling from individuals with lived experience and service provider
 s before the walk begins.\n\nWinter Walk is rooted in the belief that endi
 ng homelessness starts with ending stigma. By walking side by side\, house
 d and unhoused\, we amplify voices too often unheard\, elevate the work of
  frontline organizations\, and affirm that homelessness is a solvable cris
 is when met with compassion\, awareness\, and collective will.\n\n*This ev
 ent is complimentary and reserved for members only. By registering for thi
 s event\, you are authorizing The 'Quin House to release your contact info
 rmation to Winter Walk. To read the full Release of Liability and Waiver\,
  click here. Members do not need to register separately through Winter Wal
 k.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/167855
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Impact Fund
END:VEVENT
