BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-169177@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T150000
SUMMARY: 90 Minutes of Innovation: Top Gun Meets a $2+ Billion Aviation Gam
 e-Changer 
LOCATION:The Pub
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 146 spots le
 ft\nStatus: You are Confirmed\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com
 /events/169177\n\n1:00PM Program\, 2:30PM Networking \nTwo frontiers. One
  stage. Not to be missed. In this high-voltage edition of 90 Minutes of In
 novation\, flight becomes more than a metaphor — it becomes a stress tes
 t for the future of AI\, defense\, climate innovation\, and human judgment
  itself.\n\nJohn Werner — venture capitalist\, Forbes AI columnist\, and
  Innovation Curator at The ’Quin House — convenes an extraordinary pai
 ring you won’t see anywhere else. A real-world Top Gun who has flown 80 
 combat missions\, 290 test missions\, and logged more than 2\,000 hours ac
 ross 30 aircraft — including the F-35\, F-15\, and F-16 — operating al
 ongside AI in live\, high-stakes environments. And a leader helping build 
 one of the most highly capitalized electric aviation companies in the worl
 d.\n\nFirst: Kristen Costello\n\nBuilding the Next Aviation System\n\nKris
 ten Costello is a pilot and executive at Vermont-based Beta Technologies\,
  a New England aerospace company valued at more than $2 billion and backed
  by over $1 billion from Fidelity\, Qatar Investment Authority\, Amazon’
 s Climate Pledge Fund\, GE Aerospace\, and others.\n\nBeta isn’t pitchin
 g a concept. It’s building a new aviation system. Founded by former Harv
 ard hockey player Kyle Clark — once told not to return to Vermont becaus
 e “there was nothing there” — Beta has grown into one of the most am
 bitious aerospace companies on the planet. The company is developing all-e
 lectric aircraft for cargo\, medical logistics\, and passenger travel whil
 e simultaneously constructing a nationwide charging network. It has comple
 ted cross-country flights\, secured major commercial and defense partnersh
 ips\, and is advancing through the FAA’s rigorous certification process.
 \n\nThe breakthrough isn’t just the airplane. It’s the systems thinkin
 g — aircraft\, charging infrastructure\, certification\, pilot training\
 , and operations built in parallel. Not incremental change\, but a redesig
 n of regional air mobility from propulsion to power grid. If it succeeds\,
  it won’t just change how we fly. It will change where flying makes sens
 e.\n\nThen: Tucker “Cinco” Hamilton\n\nWhere Humans and AI Share the C
 ockpit\n\nThe evening shifts to contested airspace.\n\nRetired U.S. Air Fo
 rce Colonel and experimental fighter test pilot Tucker “Cinco” Hamilto
 n — former Chief of AI Test and Operations for the U.S. Air Force and Sp
 ace Force — led the integration of AI-enabled autonomy into combat aircr
 aft. He has operated at the edge\, where algorithms and humans share the c
 ockpit in real-time\, high-consequence environments.\n\nHamilton brings au
 diences inside moments few will ever experience: ejecting from a failing a
 ircraft\, managing an engine fire at twice the speed of sound\, crash-land
 ing a jet while fighting to keep it upright\, and flying combat missions o
 ver Afghanistan. For Hamilton\, AI is not theoretical. It is airborne. He 
 has confronted the defining questions of our era:\n\nWhen should a machine
  be trusted?\n\nHow do you test systems that learn?\n\nWhat happens when A
 I evolves faster than doctrine?\n\nWho is accountable when autonomy acts?\
 n\nThis program also marks the debut of his new book\, Unlocking the Last 
 20%\, on elite performance in an age of automation.\n\nAviation has always
  previewed the future. Now it is revealing the operating system of the nex
 t century. The future is not humans replaced by machines. It is humans red
 esigned alongside them.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for m
 embers only. Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/169177
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
