BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-173833@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260304T140928Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T210000
SUMMARY:Author's Circle Book Club: "Canticle" with Janet Rich Edwards 
LOCATION:The Muse
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 15 spots left\nS
 tatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/17383
 3\n\nBookmark the date for a compelling conversation exploring Canticle\, 
 the luminous debut novel by Janet Rich Edwards set in thirteenth-century B
 ruges - a story of faith\, independence\, and love.\n\nAt sixteen\, Aleys 
 is serious\, stubborn\, and prone to religious visions. When her closest c
 ompanion abandons her for the monastery and her family promises her in mar
 riage to the calculating head of the weavers’ guild\, she refuses to acc
 ept the life chosen for her. Fleeing home\, she finds refuge among the Beg
 uines - an independent community of religious women who live and worship o
 utside the authority of the Church.\n\nWithin this vibrant sisterhood\, Al
 eys discovers scholarship\, friendship\, and a new sense of purpose. But a
 s illicit translations of scripture circulate and reports of miracles spre
 ad\, the women’s autonomy draws dangerous scrutiny from Church authoriti
 es - forcing Aleys to confront the true cost of devotion\, love\, and sacr
 ifice.\n\nJoin us for a thoughtful discussion of this richly imagined hist
 orical novel and its stirring portrait of spiritual awakening and female a
 gency.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members only. Ligh
 t bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/173833
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
